    <legend class="form-outline">REGISTRATION</legend>
    <div class="form-group col">
    A Registration Form & Waiver must be completed and submitted by a parent or legal guardian before any class is taken.
    
    <p><p>There is a $20 registration fee. If you discontinue classes for any reason for more than one month, and then return, you will be required to pay the registration fee upon re-enrolling.
    </div>

    <legend class="form-outline">TUITION</legend>
    <div class="form-group col">
    Tuition for classes is a monthly tuition (regardless of the number of weeks or holidays in any month). Please see Holidays Closed on our website.
    
    <p><p>Tuition is paid in advance and is due on the 1st day of each month.  We accept credit card payments and offer a recurring payment option.  If your first class falls on a holiday or you are absent, you may pay online or mail your tuition payment to Pacific Dance, BUT it must be postmarked before the 7th day of the month in order to avoid a $15 late fee. 
    
    <p><p>NO statements will be mailed to you unless your tuition is late.
    
    <p><p>A $15 late fee will be charged for all tuition payments received after the 7th day of the month (including payments mailed and postdated after the 7th day of the month). 
    
    <p><p>A $35 fee will be charged on all returned checks.
    
    <p><p>NO credit or refund is given for absences, tuition, costumes, competition fees or convention fees.
    
    <p><p>If you are dropping classes, you must notify us via e-mail by the 20th day of the preceding month, or you will be responsible to pay your tuition for the following month.
    
    <p><p>We offer a recurring credit card charge to be charged on the 1st day of each month.  You must notify us via e-mail by the 20th of the month preceding the month you would like to drop, so we can deactivate your recurring charge.
    </div>
    
    <legend class="form-outline">ABSENCES</legend>
    <div class="form-group col">
    If you are absent from a class, you may use a courtesy make-up in a comparable class.  A make-up must be taken no later than one month from the date of the absence, and you must be currently registered in a class.  Make-ups are non-transferrable. Pacific Dance has the right to refuse the use of a make-up should the class size be too large on the day of a make-up, or if the level/age is not appropriate for the student (refer to Class Schedules page on our website for a list of classes closed or with limited make-ups).
    
    <p><p>If you are taking a make-up class in a 90 minute class and are not enrolled in a 90 minute class, you will need to use two make-ups to take a make-up in a 90 minute class.
    </div>

    <legend class="form-outline">ATTIRE</legend>
    <div class="form-group col">
